# Commit and push after changes

After completing any code change in this project:

1. Run `npm run build` when the change touches app code (unless the user skipped verification).
2. Commit with a concise message focused on why.
3. Push to `origin main` without being asked again.

Do not leave completed work uncommitted. Only skip commit/push if the user explicitly says not to, or if there are no file changes.
